main event: A witness observed a bright white object in the sky over Dayton, Ohio in October 1965.
interesting points: The object appeared to be a boomerang shape with a bump in the middle and was described as a bright white light.
The object seemed to move at a high speed of 2-3 degrees every 5 minutes.
No sound was described in the report.
The witness compared the brightness of the object to something similar to the planet Venus.
The object was observed for around 30 minutes.
